.TH REMOM 6 "2026" "ReMoM" "Games"
.SH NAME
ReMoM \- reassembly of Master of Magic v1.31
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ReMoM
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ReMoM
is a source-code reconstruction of
.IR "Master of Magic" ,
the 1994 turn-based fantasy strategy game by Simtex, rebuilt in C from a
disassembly of the original DOS executable.
.B ReMoM
is the player executable.
.PP
This package contains the game engine only. It ships
.B no
game content. You must own a copy of Master of Magic v1.31 (DOS) and supply its
data files \(em every
.I *.LBX
plus
.I CONFIG.MOM
\(em yourself.
.B ReMoM
locates them through an ordered search path and will show an error dialog rather
than crash if they cannot be found. Run without options to play normally.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-continue
Resume the most recent save on startup, skipping the main menu.
.TP
.BI \-\-load " FILE"
Load the named save game on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-orig\-files
Re-seed the per-user working copies of
.IR CONFIG.MOM ,
.I MAGIC.SET
and
.I SAVE1\-9.GAM
from the original game data, first moving the current copies into a timestamped
.RI backup\- YYYYMMDD \- HHMMSS
directory so nothing is lost.
.TP
.B \-\-headless
Run without opening a window. Intended for automated testing.
.TP
.BI \-\-record " FILE"
Record the input stream to
.I FILE
for later replay.
.TP
.BI \-\-replay " FILE"
Replay a previously recorded input stream.
.TP
.BI \-\-demo " [FILE]"
Replay
.I FILE
as a demo, defaulting to
.I DEMO.RMR
when no filename is given.
.TP
.BI \-\-capture " DIR"
Write captured frames to
.IR DIR .
.TP
.BI \-\-capture\-fps " N"
Capture at
.I N
frames per second. May appear before or after
.BR \-\-capture .
.TP
.BI \-\-scenario " FILE"
Load and run a scripted scenario.
.TP
.BI \-\-patch " NAME"
Select a named data-patch scenario, applied after every save load. Inert unless
named.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B REMOM_DATA_DIR
Directory holding the original Master of Magic data files. Takes precedence over
every other entry in the search path.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Saved games,
.I MAGIC.SET
and
.I CONFIG.MOM
working copies are kept in
.IR $XDG_DATA_HOME/ReMoM/ ,
by default
.IR ~/.local/share/ReMoM/ .
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
.I ReMoM.ini
is read from
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/ReMoM/ ,
by default
.IR ~/.config/ReMoM/ .
.TP
.B XDG_STATE_HOME
Log files are written to
.IR $XDG_STATE_HOME/ReMoM/ ,
by default
.IR ~/.local/state/ReMoM/ .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/remom/PLAYING.md
Player guide: supplying game data, save locations, troubleshooting.
.SH NOTES
Your original Master of Magic installation is treated as read-only and is never
modified.
.B ReMoM
seeds its own working copies on first run and reads and writes only those.
.SH BUGS
Report issues at
.I https://github.com/jbalcomb/ReMoM/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
Project home:
.I https://github.com/jbalcomb/ReMoM
